# The kind harness scripts run on Linux CI runners (and local Linux/macOS); they
# MUST check out with LF line endings. Under core.autocrlf=true these files would
# materialize CRLF in the working tree, and a CRLF shebang / `set -o pipefail`
# line breaks the script on Linux (the shell sees `\r` as part of the command).
# Pinning eol=lf here keeps every harness artifact LF regardless of the cloner's
# autocrlf setting — mirrors deploy/kubernetes/.gitattributes (the same CRLF trap
# silently produced a false-green policy gate there, ADR-0029 §5).
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.yml  text eol=lf
